# Startup & Global Workflow

At the start of every session or when "loading", the agent MUST:
1. Initialize by following the Global Workflow: `/global-workflow`
2. Read `ARCHITECTURE.md` and `DIRECTIVES.md` to ensure operational compliance.
3. Check the current focused Task in `.gsd/ROADMAP.md`.

---

# Global Deploy Rule

Whenever asked to "Deploy" or "Push to Live", execute the following steps to trigger the CI/CD pipeline:

1. Stage all changes: `git add .`
2. Commit changes with a descriptive message: `git commit -m "feat/fix/chore: <description>"`
3. Push to master: `git push origin master`

Wait for the GitHub Actions pipeline (`.github/workflows/deploy.yml`) to finish building and deploying the changes to the Live VPS automatically. Do not attempt to SSH into the remote server manually unless the GitHub Action fails.
